# vble Interventions_new: Generaremos una nueva variable que indique el tipo de la intervenciÃ³n 
    # Behavioral/Radiation/Diagnostic/Device/Biological/Drug/Genetic/Procedure/Others

data['Behavioral'] = data['Interventions'].str.contains('Behavioral', regex=False)

data['Diagnostic'] = data['Interventions'].str.contains('Diagnostic Test', regex=False)
data['Device'] = data['Interventions'].str.contains('Device', regex=False)
data['Biological'] = data['Interventions'].str.contains('Biological', regex=False)
data['Drug'] = data['Interventions'].str.contains('Drug', regex=False)
data['Genetic'] = data['Interventions'].str.contains('Genetic', regex=False)
data['Procedure'] = data['Interventions'].str.contains('Procedure', regex=False)

# Definimos 3 macros para 3 tablas de contingencia 

# Tabla de contingencia
def tabla_cont (vble1, vble2):
    return pd.crosstab(index = data[vble1], columns=data[vble2], margins=True)

# tabla de contingencia en porcentajes relativos total
def tabla_cont_pctn (vble1, vble2):
    return pd.crosstab(index = data[vble1],columns=data[vble2], margins=True).apply(lambda r: r/len(data) *100, axis=1)

# tabla de contingencia en porcentajes relativos segun fila (vble1)
def tabla_cont_rowpctn (vble1, vble2):
    return pd.crosstab(index = data[vble1],columns=data[vble2]).apply(lambda r: r/r.sum() *100, axis=1)

# tabla de contingencia en porcentajes relativos segun fila (vble1)
def tabla_cont_colpctn (vble1, vble2):
    return pd.crosstab(index = data[vble1],columns=data[vble2]).apply(lambda r: r/r.sum() *100, axis=0)

# Asignamos la media a los na para no tener q eliminar registros a la hora de modelar.
data['Enrollment'] = data['Enrollment'].fillna(data['Enrollment'].mean())
data['Duration'] = data['Duration'].fillna(data['Duration'].mean())
data['Duration_real'] = data['Duration_real'].fillna(data['Duration_real'].mean())
data['Time_First_Posted'] = data['Time_First_Posted'].fillna(data['Time_First_Posted'].mean())
data['yrs_Study'] = data['yrs_Study'].fillna(data['yrs_Study'].mean())

In [116]:
clf=clf2
n_nodes = clf.tree_.node_count
children_left = clf.tree_.children_left
children_right = clf.tree_.children_right
feature = clf.tree_.feature
threshold = clf.tree_.threshold
node_depth = np.zeros(shape=n_nodes, dtype=np.int64)
is_leaves = np.zeros(shape=n_nodes, dtype=bool)

stack = [(0, 0)]  # start with the root node id (0) and its depth (0)
while len(stack) > 0:
    # `pop` ensures each node is only visited once
    node_id, depth = stack.pop()
    node_depth[node_id] = depth

    # If the left and right child of a node is not the same we have a split
    # node
    is_split_node = children_left[node_id] != children_right[node_id]
    # If a split node, append left and right children and depth to `stack`
    # so we can loop through them
    if is_split_node:
        stack.append((children_left[node_id], depth + 1))
        stack.append((children_right[node_id], depth + 1))
    else:
        is_leaves[node_id] = True

print("The binary tree structure has {n} nodes and has "
      "the following tree structure:\n".format(n=n_nodes))
for i in range(n_nodes):
    if is_leaves[i]:
        print("{space}node={node} is a leaf node.".format(
            space=node_depth[i] * "\t", node=i))
    else:
        print("{space}node={node} is a split node: "
              "go to node {left} if X[:, {feature}] <= {threshold} "
              "else to node {right}.".format(
                  space=node_depth[i] * "\t",
                  node=i,
                  left=children_left[i],
                  feature=feature[i],
                  threshold=threshold[i],
                  right=children_right[i]))

The binary tree structure has 15 nodes and has the following tree structure:

node=0 is a split node: go to node 1 if X[:, 11] <= 14.5 else to node 8.
	node=1 is a split node: go to node 2 if X[:, 11] <= 3.5 else to node 5.

	node=8 is a split node: go to node 9 if X[:, 9] <= 0.5 else to node 12.
